<h2 class="section-head">How to Brew <em>Ethiopian Coffee Well</em></h2>

<p class="body">Ethiopian coffees, especially washed light-to-medium roasts from Yirgacheffe and Guji, are best showcased in brewing methods that preserve clarity and allow floral and citrus notes to come through without muddying them. Pour-over (V60, Chemex, Kalita) is the classic choice: clean paper filtration, medium-fine grind, water at around 200 degrees Fahrenheit, a 1:15 to 1:16 coffee-to-water ratio.</p>

<p class="body">Avoid French press for washed light Ethiopian if you want to experience the full floral character; the metal filter lets fines through that add body and bitterness, which mutes the delicate notes that make Yirgacheffe distinctive. For natural Ethiopian coffees, which have more body and intensity built in, French press is a reasonable choice and adds to the cup's richness.</p>

